        "body" : "Prefixing a variable with `local` (or `export`) suppresses any errors during RHS evaluation.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ function foo { VAR=$(false); echo $?; }; foo\r\n1\r\n$ function foo { local VAR=$(false); echo $?; }; foo\r\n0\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you need to crash if this line fails, then you might need to separate the `local` part. I tend to just move it to the top of the file, C-style:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncheck() {\r\n    local sha ver ver_sha\r\n    # rest of function\r\n}\r\n```",
